  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are some cool Pok\u00e9mon GO gadgets to buy?",
  "response": "There are several cool gadgets that can enhance your Pok\u00e9mon GO experience. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **Pok\u00e9mon GO Plus**: This is a small Bluetooth device that allows you to catch Pok\u00e9mon and collect items from Pok\u00e9Stops without having to take out your phone. It vibrates and lights up to notify you when a Pok\u00e9mon is nearby or when you can collect items.\n\n2. **Pok\u00e9mon GO Plus +**: An upgraded version of the original Pok\u00e9mon GO Plus, this device offers all the features of the original and adds sleep tracking functionality.\n\n3. **Smartwatches**: Certain smartwatches, like the Apple Watch or Android Wear devices, can be used to play Pok\u00e9mon GO. They allow you to receive notifications, track your steps, and sometimes even interact with the game.\n\n4. **External Battery Pack**: Pok\u00e9mon GO can drain your phone's battery quickly, especially with location services and game graphics. A high-capacity portable charger can keep you in the game longer without worrying about battery life.\n\n5. **Phone Holder or Arm Band**: A good phone holder or arm band can help you keep your hands free while you\u2019re walking or biking, making it easier to enjoy the game.\n\n6. **Fitness Tracker**: Wearable fitness trackers like Fitbit or Garmin can help you monitor your steps and distance, which is useful for hatching eggs and earning candy from your buddy Pok\u00e9mon.\n\n7. **Screen Magnifier**: A screen magnifier can help enlarge the game display, making it easier to see Pok\u00e9mon and Pok\u00e9Stops from a distance.\n\n8. **Bluetooth Headset**: A good pair of wireless earbuds can enhance the Pok\u00e9mon GO experience by allowing you to hear in-game sounds and notifications more clearly while also staying mobile.\n\n9. **Custom Phone Case**: A sturdy custom phone case can protect your device while you\u2019re out exploring, and some cases are designed specifically for gamers with extra grip or built-in kickstands.\n\n10. **AR Glasses**: If you want to take your Pok\u00e9mon GO experience to the next level, look for augmented reality glasses that can overlay Pok\u00e9mon onto the real world without needing to look at your phone constantly.\n\nWhen choosing gadgets, consider what features are most important for your playstyle and whether you need something for convenience, better gameplay, or enhanced experience.",
